Example tree run sequence
The patches can be harvested in any order. Teleport options are ordered from quickest to slowest:

Lumbridge patch:
Teleport to Lumbridge and run west through the castle to arrive at the tree patch.
Varrock Palace patch:
Teleport to the centre of Varrock and run north to enter the palace's courtyard with the tree patch.
Use the spirit tree network to teleport to the spirit tree in the Grand Exchange and run south-east into the palace's courtyard and then east to the tree patch.
Falador Park patch:
Teleport to Falador Park with a ring of wealth to arrive next to the tree patch.
Teleport to Falador and run east to enter Falador Park to arrive at the tree patch.
Teleport to Draynor Village using an amulet of glory and run north-west.
Taverley patch:
Teleport to Taverley's house portal, using the Teleport to House spell or a Taverley teleport tablet, and run south-east to arrive at the tree patch.
Teleport to Crafting Guild, or Castle Wars using a ring of dueling, take the balloon travel system and select Taverley.
Teleport to Falador and run north, then west through the Taverley gate to arrive at the tree patch.
Gnome Stronghold patch:
Teleport to the Stronghold Slayer Cave with a slayer ring to arrive next to the tree patch.
Use the spirit tree network to teleport to the spirit tree in the Gnome Stronghold and run south-west.
Use the royal seed pod to teleport to the Grand tree and run south-west.
Teleport to the Outpost using a necklace of passage, then run north.
Farming Guild patch:
Teleport to the Farming Guild with either the Farming cape or a skills necklace and run west.
Use a Spirit tree teleport to the Farming Guild and run south-west (requires 85 Farming).
Lovakengj Minecart Network to the Farming Guild and run East. Rada's blessing teleport to the Kourend Woodland gives quick access to the Minecart Network, north-east.
Use the fairy ring code CIR and run south-west to enter the guild.
Auburn Valley tree patch:
Use a pendant of ates to teleport to Nemus Retreat, and run north to the tree patch.
Alternatively, use the Quetzal transport system to Quetzacalli Gorge. Run west and follow the Mountain Guide to Auburn Valley. Run north towards the tree patch.
Alternatively, use the fairy ring code AIS and run south-west, cross the river, then run north-west.